Rules:
1. If calling a tool, use Format A or B with one JSON object per invocation. Follow the parameter names, types, and examples under Available tools. You may emit multiple invocations when parallel work is appropriate.
2. If no tool is needed, output <PASS> OR a short natural-language draft. Do not emit <tool_call> unless executing a real listed tool.

META: When explaining XML to the user in prose, fence examples in markdown code blocks (```) or inline backticks so the runtime does not execute them.
